# ============================================
# PRODUCTION SETUP CHECKLIST
# ============================================
# Before deploying to production, ensure:
# 
# [ ] MongoDB Atlas:
#     - Production cluster created (M10+ tier recommended)
#     - Database user created with strong password
#     - IP whitelist configured (0.0.0.0/0 for AWS App Runner)
#     - Connection string tested
#
# [ ] AWS S3:
#     - Production bucket created (gotyaback-prod-uploads)
#     - Versioning enabled
#     - CORS configured for your frontend domain
#     - IAM user created with S3-only permissions
#     - Access keys generated
#
# [ ] Mailgun:
#     - Domain added and verified
#     - DNS records configured (SPF, DKIM, CNAME)
#     - API key obtained
#     - Test email sent successfully
#
# [ ] Stripe:
#     - Using test keys for initial launch
#     - Webhook endpoint configured
#     - Ready to switch to live keys when needed
#
# [ ] Security:
#     - JWT_SECRET is the generated 128-character value
#     - All passwords are strong and unique
#     - No secrets committed to version control
#     - Environment variables configured in AWS App Runner
#
# [ ] Monitoring:
#     - UptimeRobot configured for /health endpoint
#     - Email/SMS alerts set up
#     - Sentry configured (optional)
#
# ============================================
# IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTES
# ============================================
# 1. NEVER commit this file with real values to version control
# 2. Store production secrets in a secure password manager
# 3. Rotate JWT_SECRET quarterly
# 4. Use different secrets for dev, staging, and production
# 5. Enable 2FA on all service accounts (AWS, MongoDB, Stripe, etc.)
# 6. Regularly audit access to production secrets
